verses:
THOU hast lifted me, my foes rejoice not o’er me, Now I will extol Thee, LORD;
Thou hast brought my soul up and hast kept me alive, I cried and Thou hast healed me;
Sing unto the LORD, ye saints and give thanks to Him, For Thou hast healed me;
O LORD my God, I will give thanks unto Thee for ever.

For His anger only lasts a moment of time;
Weeping may endure a night;
In the morning, no more weeping, Oh what a joy!
I cried and Thou hast heard me;
By Thy favour Thou hast made my mountain to stand, For Thou hast heard me;
O LORD my God, I will give thanks unto Thee for ever.

Thou hast turned my mourning into dancing for me, Thou hast put off my sackcloth;
Thou hast turned my mourning into dancing for me, And girded me with gladness
To the end my glory may sing praise unto Thee, And not be silent;
O LORD my God, I will give thanks unto Thee for ever.

WE’VE heard, O God, with our ears what work
Thou didst of old,
How Thou didst drive out heathen with Thy hand.
They got not land in possession by their strength and sword, But because Thou hadst favour unto them.

Thou art King, Thou art King, Thou art my King O God;
Through Thy Name we will push down our enemies.
Thou art King, Thou art King, Thou art my King O God;
Through Thy Name we will push down our enemies.

I’ll not trust my bow, nor shall my sword save me;
In God we boast all the day long, and praise Thy Name for e’er.
Thou hast saved us from all them that hated us;
In God we boast all the day long, and praise Thy Name for e’er.

If we’ve forgotten the Name of our Almighty God, Or stretched out our hands to a heathen god,
He’ll search this out, for He knows the secrets of the heart;
Yet we’ve not forgotten Thy covenant.

Thou art King, Thou art King, Thou art my King O God;
Through Thy Name we will push down our enemies.
Thou art King, Thou art King, Thou art my King O God;
Through Thy Name we will push down our enemies.

Yea, for thy sake are we killed all the day long;
Our heart is not turned from Thy way, we’ll praise Thy Name for e’er.
Cast us not away, arise to be our help;
Our heart is not turned from Thy way, we’ll praise Thy Name for e’er.

Wise men die and also fools and leave their wealth behind;
Men within themselves do think their house shall last for e’er.
Oh the folly of their way, and foolish men approve their words,
In the grave like sheep they’re laid, all their beauty disappears;
And the upright shall rule over them; The grave then shall be their dwelling.

The LORD gives eyesight to the blind;
The LORD supports the fainting mind;
He sends the labouring conscience peace;
He helps the stranger in distress,
The widow and the fatherless,
And grants the prisoner sweet release.

He loves His saints, He knows them well,
But turns the wicked down to hell;
Thy God, O Zion, ever reigns!
Let every tongue, let every age,
In this exalted work engage;
Praise Him with everlasting strains.

chorus:
Praise ye the LORD, praise ye the LORD,
His Name alone is exalted;
Praise ye the LORD, sun and moon so bright;
Let all the earth worship Him.

verses:
Praise ye the LORD, the hosts in the heavens:
Praise ye the LORD, sun and moon so bright;
Praise Him all ye stars of light far above;
Praise Him all ye clouds above.

Praise ye the LORD, O praise ye the LORD,
Praise ye the LORD in His sanctuary;
Praise Him in the firmament of His power;
Praise Him for His mighty acts.

chorus:
Lord, Thou art worthy; Lord,
Thou art worthy;
Lord, Thou art worthy and worthy alone;
Blessed in Thy presence, we worship
before Thee,
Own Thou art worthy and worthy alone.

verses:
Behold how the shepherds, summoned to His cradle,
Leaving their flocks, draw nigh with lowly fear;
We too will thither bend our joyful footsteps;
O come let us adore Him,
O come let us adore Him,
O come let us adore Him, Christ the Lord.

In the heavenly country bright
Need they no created light;
Thou its light, its joy, its crown,
Thou its sun which goes not down;
There for ever may we sing
Hallelujahs to our King.

Come to this fountain so rich and sweet,
Cast thy poor soul at the Saviour’s feet;
Plunge in today and be made complete;
Glory to His Name!

My heart is bubbling and full
With joy abundant and free;
O Lord, how wonderful
Are all Thy workings in me;
From morn to evening, from e'en to morning,
Thou art so praiseworthy;
From morn to evening, from e'en to morning,
Thou art so praiseworthy,
Thou art so praiseworthy.

He'll never, never leave me, nor yet forsake me here
While I live by faith and do His blessed will;
A wall of fire around me, I've nothing now to fear;
With His manna He my hungry soul shall fill;
Then sweeping up to glory,
I'll see His blessed face
Where rivers of delight shall ever flow.
He's the Lily of the Valley,
The Bright and Morning Star,
He's the fairest of ten thousand to my soul.

Other refuge have I none;
Hangs my helpless soul on Thee;
Leave, ah! leave me not alone,
Still support and comfort me.
All my trust on Thee is stayed,
All my help from Thee I bring;
Cover my defenceless head
With the shadow of Thy wing.
